  "prompt": "What are the places to explore near Nagpur?",
  "response": "Nagpur, located in the central part of India, offers various interesting places to explore in its vicinity. Here are some notable destinations:\n\n1. **Pench National Park**: Situated around 88 km from Nagpur, this national park is known for its wildlife, including tigers, leopards, and various bird species. It's a great spot for safari lovers.\n\n2. **Tadoba-Andhari Tiger Reserve**: Approximately 140 km from Nagpur, this is one of the largest and oldest national parks in Maharashtra, famous for its tiger population.\n\n3. **Sevagram**: About 75 km from Nagpur, Sevagram is known for the ashram established by Mahatma Gandhi, offering a glimpse into his life and philosophy.\n\n4. **Ramtek**: Located nearly 50 km from Nagpur, Ramtek has historical significance and is home to ancient temples, including the Ramtek Fort Temple dedicated to Lord Rama.\n\n5. **Ambazari Lake and Garden**: Within Nagpur itself, it is one of the biggest lakes and offers a serene environment with gardens, a musical fountain, and boating facilities.\n\n6. **Mansar**: Roughly 50 km away, this archaeological site provides insights into the remnants of an ancient city.\n\n7. **Khindsi Lake**: Approximately 45 km from Nagpur, this is a popular spot for water sports and picnics.\n\n8. **Bor Wildlife Sanctuary**: Located around 63 km from Nagpur, it is another excellent destination for wildlife enthusiasts.\n\nThese places offer varied experiences, from history and culture to nature and adventure.",
